The paper deals with image processing tasks and fully convolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the generalization abilities of FCNs, which falls under the scope of machine learning and deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also explores the relationship between batch sizes and the loss surface, which is related to optimization techniques. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the skip-layer connections in FCNs, which can be considered as a natural language processing task. Hence, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely but possible sub-category.
